meta {
  name: Agent Identity (auth.md POST /agent/identity)
  type: http
  seq: 97
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/agent/identity
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "type": "service_auth",
    "login_hint": "{{accountEmail}}"
  }
}

vars:pre-request {
  baseUrl: http://localhost:8080
}

docs {
  # POST /agent/identity

  The auth.md agent-registration endpoint (auth.md spec Step 3). Dispatches on the request `type`.
  Every flow is opt-in per operator via `[agent_auth]` in `pds.toml` (all off by default), so a
  fresh install answers each request with the flow's `*_not_enabled` error until configured.

  ## service_auth (shown above)

  The agent knows only the user's email (`login_hint`). Starts a claim ceremony bound to the
  matching local account and returns the claim materials:

  ```json
  {
    "registration_id": "reg_...",
    "registration_type": "service_auth",
    "claim_token": "clm_...",
    "claim": { "user_code": "...", "verification_uri": "https://.../agent/claim", "expires_at": "..." }
  }
  ```

  Requires `[agent_auth] service_auth_enabled = true`.

  ## identity_assertion

  Body: `{ "type": "identity_assertion", "assertion": "<ID-JAG JWT>" }` (optional
  `"assertion_type": "urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:id-jag"`). The ID-JAG is verified against a
  configured `[[agent_auth.trusted_issuers]]` entry (signature, `iss`, `aud`, `exp`, and
  `auth_time` freshness). A confirmed `(iss, sub)` returns 200 with a service-signed
  `identity_assertion`; a first-seen `(iss, sub)` whose email matches a local account returns
  401 `interaction_required` with a claim block to confirm.

  ## anonymous

  Body: `{ "type": "anonymous" }`. Registers an ownerless pre-claim identity (no user identity yet;
  `agent_identities.did` is NULL until a claim binds one). Returns 200 with a pre-claim
  `identity_assertion` carrying the operator's `pre_claim_scopes` plus a `claim_token` for an
  optional later claim ceremony:

  ```json
  {
    "registration_id": "reg_...",
    "registration_type": "anonymous",
    "identity_assertion": "<service-signed pre-claim assertion>",
    "assertion_expires": "...",
    "scopes": ["atproto", "repo:*?action=create&action=update", "blob:*/*"],
    "claim_token": "clm_..."
  }
  ```

  Requires `[agent_auth] anonymous_enabled = true`. The identity stays unclaimed, so the pre-claim
  assertion cannot yet be exchanged at the token endpoint (the jwt-bearer grant requires a claimed
  identity).

  ## Errors (OAuth-style `{ "error", "error_description" }` body)

  - 400 invalid_request: missing/unknown `type`, or a flow's required field is absent
  - 400 service_auth_not_enabled / anonymous_not_enabled: the flow is disabled by config
  - 403 issuer_not_enabled: the ID-JAG `iss` is not on the trust list
  - 400/403 access_denied: no local account matches the asserted identity / login_hint
  - 401 invalid_grant: the ID-JAG is malformed or fails verification
  - 401 login_required: the ID-JAG `auth_time` is too stale
  - 401 interaction_required: a new binding needs user confirmation (carries a `claim` block)
}
